Note: `.js` extensions on every relative import — required by Node16 module resolution with `"type": "module"`.

**Type definitions at top of file:**

```typescript
export type ProductWithDetails = Product & {
  isLowStock: boolean;
  inventoryValue: number;
};

export type ProductListResult = {
  products: Product[];
  summary: {
    count: number;
    totalInventoryValue: number;
    averagePrice: number;
  };
};
```

**`listProducts` function:**

Accepts an optional filters object to keep the signature clean:

```typescript
export interface ProductFilters {
  category?: string;
  minPrice?: number;
  maxPrice?: number;
}

export function listProducts(filters: ProductFilters = {}): ProductListResult {
  let filtered = [...products];

  if (filters.category !== undefined) {
    filtered = filtered.filter((p) => p.category === filters.category);
  }
  if (filters.minPrice !== undefined) {
    filtered = filtered.filter((p) => p.price >= filters.minPrice!);
  }
  if (filters.maxPrice !== undefined) {
    filtered = filtered.filter((p) => p.price <= filters.maxPrice!);
  }

  const totalValue = filtered.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.price * p.stock, 0);
  const avgPrice =
    filtered.length > 0
      ? filtered.reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.price, 0) / filtered.length
      : 0;

  return {
    products: filtered,
    summary: {
      count: filtered.length,
      totalInventoryValue: Math.round(totalValue * 100) / 100,
      averagePrice: Math.round(avgPrice * 100) / 100,
    },
  };
}
```

The route will parse query params and call this with already-converted numeric values. The `NaN` guard moves to the route (it is a parsing concern, not domain logic).

**`getProductById` function:**

```typescript
export function getProductById(id: number): ProductWithDetails {
  const product = products.find((p) => p.id === id);
  if (!product) {
    throw new AppError("Product not found", 404);
  }
  return {
    ...product,
    isLowStock: product.stock < 10,
    inventoryValue: Math.round(product.price * product.stock * 100) / 100,
  };
}
```

**`updateProductStock` function:**

```typescript
export function updateProductStock(
  id: number,
  adjustment: number
): ProductWithDetails {
  const product = products.find((p) => p.id === id);
  if (!product) {
    throw new AppError("Product not found", 404);
  }

  const newStock = product.stock + adjustment;
  if (newStock < 0) {
    throw new AppError("Insufficient stock", 400);
  }

  product.stock = newStock;

  return {
    ...product,
    isLowStock: product.stock < 10,
    inventoryValue: Math.round(product.price * product.stock * 100) / 100,
  };
}
```

The `typeof adjustment !== "number"` check remains in the route (shape/type parsing). This service function receives a guaranteed `number`.

